    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-06-04T17:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-06-04T17:00:00-05:00" n="410"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d410">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Minister in the Dominican Republic</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Russell</hi>
                    </persName>)<note n="1" xml:id="d410fn1">The same, <hi rend="italic">mutatis
                            mutandis</hi>, on the same date, to the Minister in Haiti.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-06-04T18:00:00-04:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">June 4, 1918, 6 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Your May 30, 8 a.m. Chinese Government has instructed its Legation here to
                    request that the consent of the Dominican Government be obtained in order that
                    American diplomatic and consular representatives may take charge of Chinese
                    interests and issue passports to Chinese citizens [proceeding to countries other
                    than the United States].<note n="2" xml:id="d410fn2">Words in brackets added by
                        telegram of June 13.</note>
                </p>
                <p>You may request desired permission and act thereunder when granted.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Phillips</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
